                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This is discussed in a <a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/upload/showthread.php?threadid=11831" target="_blank" class="postlink">thread at EQTraders</a>.  Jewelry made with enchanted metals now sell for less than jewelry made with unenchanted metals.  It appears that Sony made a sweep of tradeskill items made with all vendor components that produced a profit, judging from comments in other forums as well.
<br />

<br />
The hitch was that before the change to failure rates on highly trivial items, the profit margin on enchanted jewelry was so low that the mandatory 5% failure rate ate it up.  Now that the failure rate is much lower for exceptional jewelers, folks were doing what you were, and turning it into "risk-free" profit.  Particularly onerous to Sony is that this is "created cash" with no risk-derived source.
<br />

<br />
It has long been a guiding principal of EQ that nobody should be able to generate money simply by sitting at a vendor.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=304783" target="_blank" class="postlink">Fallere T`Vala</a>
<br />
Phantasmist of <a href="http://www.tuatha.cc" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tuatha de Danann</a>
<br />
The Tribunal</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
