                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">JC is probably 4th in cost due to plat to hit 250 on, behind fishing, baking and brewing (tinkering and make poison I've never done).
<br />
It's probably the 2nd quickest to hit 250 on due to it being all store bought. Brewing can get to 248 with store stuff so I'll hedge and say it's the quickest.
<br />

<br />
JC is probably not going to drop below pottery, smithing or tailoring in terms of cost. You can easily spend 100k in each of those and not hit 250. Having a guaranteed buy back of 90% or so of the cost is something that the three skills above would kill for. Many of the items that people use to skill up on sell for much less than cost *and* that's when you can even sell them - you're reliant on people actually wanting to buy rather than an NPC merchant.
<br />
On top of all this, when/if it actually gets fixed (again), JCM is the only tradeskill AA that is not given to all classes that can use. My original JC character is a shaman, he got 250 + Trophy a long time before AAs were introduced - my chanter did pottery to 250 pre-JCM too.
<br />

<br />
JC used to be the most unbalanced of all tradeskills (it's still pretty unbalanced when JCM is actually working). There's almost always been a large number of people skilling up on it almost throughout EQ's life. None of the others really took off at all until around the time that the Solstice quest appeared. Before this you could find out who the highest skilled smith/tailor/potter were on your server as there was invariably only one person doing it (and they became famous for actually having enough spare time to waste on it). Not only that but, when you finally caught up with them, they were hardly ever max skill anyway. Whereas there were a great number of 250 (and 200 pre-cap movement) jewellers selling Platinum (and then Velium) items in the pre-bazaar merchant zones.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=317507" target="_blank" class="postlink">Reph Rayne</a>
<br />
Bristlebane</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
